Ck2JG_tzCN9rin4psk1hPRSHd-xbVIj1XB76VBAEtURwshsGXrWZMcCQ4dLvR5892JcWZFV1QoK3hffvrPEcpb43a8re9kxc7-J5MErme5ktVHjckSqJMD-klucr2qpxGQWGQnb5b8wwLkPUVzNakNBXOuldcAz7PsB4hv2lLS6n2zVrL4kvja-hH6m-JXW9KNcLasAl_ndKCnOXhHFMyrXefEzIFYTbw0QolpfKlTUaIL0Ma4DRwDUttnRkOZ02MZmSxhRz2JxMBkDIOBs7httmbNoOj1cRmM8hk1Mt5NQ6YcZ8pu7z1A==\\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering metadata for tests**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about whether we need metadata for the TypeSamples field. It seems like user code reflection is often allowed, but the native image usually doesn’t support getDeclaredFields unless registered. But the agent might only include libraries due to a user code filter. Existing tests rely on navigator.getDeclaredFields for BeanWithFields, which complicates things. I need to figure out how to run our tests in native without relying on reflection metadata. Maybe avoiding reflection on test classes is a better route.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Reflecting on generic array fields**\\\\n\\\\nI'm trying to figure out if I can use public JDK reflection on generic array fields. I wonder if I really need a public JDK class for this. It seems like Navigator.getFieldType needs a Field object, which I can obtain from registered public classes. However, relying on native reflection might not be the best approach. Instead, I could manually construct a GenericArrayType and avoid using reflection. It’s essential to minimize dynamic access and ensure my implementation focuses on using ParameterizedType effectively. I just want to make sure it's all set correctly!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Implementing ParameterizedType**\\\\n\\\\nI need a class for ParameterizedType, and I could use my own implementation. It seems like using custom GenericArrayType classes might work, especially since the existing ReflectionNavigatorTest has ClassBackedGenericArrayType and SingleArgumentParameterizedType. However, I want to avoid sharing a dedicated file. It feels like implementing GenericArrayType manually would be the way to go. I need to ensure the component parameterized type points to raw List.class and actual String.class, which should simplify things. I’ll also check the need for Field imports!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_DzPdl8Tofz1t7unUCGNGR7jI|fc_0676a53a9aff29b00169f07179c84881a29b5ca609a192de4d\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.glassfish.jaxb/jaxb-core/3.0.0-M5/src/test/java/org_glassfish_jaxb/jaxb_core/ReflectionNavigatorAnonymous6Test.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import java.lang.reflect.GenericArrayType;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Type;\\nimport java.util.List;\\n\", \"newText\": \"import java.lang.reflect.GenericArrayType;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.ParameterizedType;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Type;\\nimport java.util.List;\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"        Navigator<Type, Class<?>, Field, Method> navigator = navigator();\\n        Field genericArrayField = navigator.getDeclaredField(TypeSamples.class, \\\"genericArray\\\");\\n        Type genericArrayType = navigator.getFieldType(genericArrayField);\\n\\n        Class<?> erasedType = navigator.asDecl(genericArrayType);\\n\\n        assertThat(genericArrayType).isInstanceOf(GenericArrayType.class);\\n        assertThat(erasedType).isSameAs(List[].class);\\n        assertThat(erasedType.getComponentType()).isSameAs(List.class);\\n\", \"newText\": \"        Navigator<Type, Class<?>, Field, Method> navigator = navigator();\\n        Type genericArrayType = new ParameterizedComponentArrayType(List.class, String.class);\\n\\n        Class<?> erasedType = navigator.asDecl(genericArrayType);\\n\\n        assertThat(erasedType).isSameAs(List[].class);\\n        assertThat(erasedType.getComponentType()).isSameAs(List.class);\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"\\n    private static final class TypeSamples {\\n        private List<String>[] genericArray;\\n    }\\n\", \"newText\": \"\\n    private static final class ParameterizedComponentArrayType implements GenericArrayType {\\n        private final ParameterizedType componentType;\\n\\n        private ParameterizedComponentArrayType(Class<?> rawType, Type argument) {\\n            componentType = new SimpleParameterizedType(rawType, argument);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Type getGenericComponentType() {\\n            return componentType;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class SimpleParameterizedType implements ParameterizedType {\\n        private final Class<?> rawType;\\n        private final Type argument;\\n\\n        private SimpleParameterizedType(Class<?> rawType, Type argument) {\\n            this.rawType = rawType;\\n            this.argument = argument;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Type[] getActualTypeArguments() {\\n            return new Type[] {argument};\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Type getRawType() {\\n            return rawType;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Type getOwnerType() {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 373, \"output\": 1306, \"cacheRead\": 37888, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 39567, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777365358034, \"responseId\": \"resp_0676a53a9aff29b00169f0716e7dac81a2bda50bed7adef28a\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_DzPdl8Tofz1t7unUCGNGR7jI|fc_0676a53a9aff29b00169f07179c84881a29b5ca609a192de4d\", \"toolName\": \"edit\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Successfully replaced 3 block(s) in tests/src/org.glassfish.jaxb/jaxb-core/3.0.0-M5/src/test/java/org_glassfish_jaxb/jaxb_core/ReflectionNavigatorAnonymous6Test.java.\"}], \"details\": {\"diff\": \"    ...\\n 10 \\n 11 import java.lang.reflect.Field;\\n 12 import java.lang.reflect.GenericArrayType;\\n 13 import java.lang.reflect.Method;\\n+14 import java.lang.reflect.ParameterizedType;\\n 14 import java.lang.reflect.Type;\\n 15 import java.util.List;\\n 16 \\n 17 import org.glassfish.jaxb.core.v2.model.nav.Navigator;\\n    ...\\n 20 public class ReflectionNavigatorAnonymous6Test {\\n 21     @Test\\n 22     public void erasesGenericArrayTypeToRuntimeArrayClass() throws Exception {\\n 23         Navigator<Type, Class<?>, Field, Method> navigator = navigator();\\n-24         Field genericArrayField = navigator.getDeclaredField(TypeSamples.class, \\\"genericArray\\\");\\n-25         Type genericArrayType = navigator.getFieldType(genericArrayField);\\n+25         Type genericArrayType = new ParameterizedComponentArrayType(List.class, String.class);\\n 26 \\n 27         Class<?> erasedType = navigator.asDecl(genericArrayType);\\n 28 \\n-29         assertThat(genericArrayType).isInstanceOf(GenericArrayType.class);\\n 30         assertThat(erasedType).isSameAs(List[].class);\\n 31         assertThat(erasedType.getComponentType()).isSameAs(List.class);\\n 32     }\\n 33 \\n    ...\\n 38         getInstance.setAccessible(true);\\n 39         return (Navigator<Type, Class<?>, Field, Method>) getInstance.invoke(null);\\n 40     }\\n 41 \\n-42     private static final class TypeSamples {\\n-43         private List<String>[] genericArray;\\n+41     private static final class ParameterizedComponentArrayType implements GenericArrayType {\\n+42         private final ParameterizedType componentType;\\n+43 \\n+44         private ParameterizedComponentArrayType(Class<?> rawType, Type argument) {\\n+45             componentType = new SimpleParameterizedType(rawType, argument);\\n+46         }\\n+47 \\n+48         @Override\\n+49         public Type getGenericComponentType() {\\n+50             return comp